16:612:41764:13:18:90:533:541:12:Times New Roman:12:Times New Roman:E:When  modeling the operating processes of ballistics and navigation support it  is expedient 
16:613:41857:18:17:62:534:523:12:Times New Roman:12:Times New Roman:B:to make decomposition  of  the  general  problem  of  coordinate-time  and  navigation  support into 
16:614:41958:17:17:62:322:506:12:Times New Roman:12:Times New Roman:B:the typical options of its engineering implementation. 
16:615:42011:17:17:90:533:489:12:Times New Roman:12:Times New Roman:E:As the satellite navigation technologies the paper considers inter-satellite measurement and 
16:616:42103:17:18:62:533:472:12:Times New Roman:12:Times New Roman:B:autonomous  navigation  mode of  differential  correction.  It  also  assesses the  possibility  of  their 
16:617:42210:18:17:62:381:454:12:Times New Roman:12:Times New Roman:B:application to improve the accuracy of navigation determinations. 
16:618:42275:17:17:90:533:437:12:Times New Roman:12:Times New Roman:E:Technologies using inter-satellite measurement tools such as GLONASS / GPS equipment, 
16:619:42360:17:17:62:533:420:12:Times New Roman:12:Times New Roman:B:equipment of inter-satellite radio link, astro-optical space based devices are an independent class 
16:620:42459:17:18:62:196:403:12:Times New Roman:12:Times New Roman:B:of navigation technologies. 
16:621:42486:18:17:90:528:385:12:Times New Roman:12:Times New Roman:C:However, each of these options has both advantages and disadvantages that affect the eval-
16:622:42576:17:17:62:336:368:12:Times New Roman:12:Times New Roman:B:uation of the appropriateness and feasibility of their use. 
16:623:42635:17:17:90:533:351:12:Times New Roman:12:Times New Roman:E:The  paper  separately considers  the  problem  of  increasing survivability  of  space  systems 
16:624:42731:17:18:62:533:334:12:Times New Roman:12:Times New Roman:B:and  conservation  of  ground  control  complex due  to  introduction  of  requirements  to  ensure  the 
16:625:42835:18:17:62:534:316:12:Times New Roman:12:Times New Roman:B:independent functioning of spacecraft and application of technologies of ballistics and navigation 
16:626:42934:17:17:62:534:299:12:Times New Roman:12:Times New Roman:B:support, supposing  to  involve minimum  means of automated  ground  control  complex for  these 
16:627:43030:17:17:62:111:282:12:Times New Roman:12:Times New Roman:B:purposes. 
16:628:43039:17:18:90:529:265:12:Times New Roman:12:Times New Roman:E:Currently, there  is a completely developed theory of autonomous  navigation based on  as-
16:629:43128:18:17:62:528:247:12:Times New Roman:12:Times New Roman:B:tronomical positional gauges, which are used as onboard optical sensors of orientation and stabi-
16:630:43224:17:17:62:145:230:12:Times New Roman:12:Times New Roman:B:lization systems. 
16:631:43241:17:18:90:533:213:12:Times New Roman:12:Times New Roman:E:To date, the differential navigation mode is, virtually, the only approach that can allow the 
16:632:43333:18:17:62:426:195:12:Times New Roman:12:Times New Roman:B:solution of tasks in terms of increased accuracy, but with some restrictions. 
16:633:43410:17:17:90:533:178:12:Times New Roman:12:Times New Roman:E:The implementation of differential mode of treatment is carried out through the creation of 
16:634:43502:17:17:62:533:161:12:Times New Roman:12:Times New Roman:B:differential subsystems of the satellite navigation systems.  These subsystems are usually divided 
16:635:43601:17:18:62:261:144:12:Times New Roman:12:Times New Roman:B:into wide-range, regional and local ones. 
16:636:43641:18:17:90:533:126:12:Times New Roman:12:Times New Roman:E:Analysis of ballistic aspects to  implement discussed navigation technologies allowed  us to 
16:637:43732:17:17:62:528:109:12:Times New Roman:12:Times New Roman:B:identify constraints for  improving accuracy to  define consumers  of  the satellite  navigation  in-
